an><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Two functions are independent if the two measurable space structures they generate are\nindependent. For a function `f` with codomain having measurable space structure `m`, the generated\nmeasurable space structure is `MeasurableSpace.comap f m`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Independence/Kernel/IndepFun.html#ProbabilityTheory.Kernel.IndepFun","kind":"def","line":52,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.Kernel.IndepFun","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Probability/Independence/Kernel/IndepFun.lean#L52-L58"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Independence/Kernel/IndepFun.html#ProbabilityTheory.Kernel.iIndepFun\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Kernel</span>.<span class=\"name\">iIndepFun</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">mα</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">mΩ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">ι</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_8</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">β</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span></span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">κ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Kernel/Defs.html#ProbabilityTheory.Kernel\">Kernel</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">MeasureTheory.Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span> := by volume_tac)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A family of functions defined on the same space `Ω` and taking values in possibly different\nspaces, each with a measurable space structure, is independent if the family of measurable space\nstructures they ge